			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Responsibilities<br />
1) Provide input to launch marketing strategies by identifying, developing and evaluating solutions based on business objectives, market sizing and characteristics, and cost and markup factors, leveraging proprietary and 3rd party research.<br />
2) Develop and manage targeted marketing campaigns and policies to promote InteraXon products and services across multiple channels, working in partnership with the Communication Manager, Event and Consumer Insights Manager and Event Coordinator, and cross-functionally with Product Management, Engineering and the Developer Team.<br />
a. Craft insightful creative briefs for agencies and suppliers.<br />
b. Maintain and develop network of contractors for creative services from writing to art direction to media buying.<br />
c. Recommend communication strategy and products to be displayed at trade or special production shows.<br />
d. Provide post-analysis reports on marketing initiatives.<br />
e. Build business case opportunities for lifecycle and retention campaigns.<br />
f. Manage budgets and ensure all projects are on time, on budget and on strategy.<br />
g. Confer with legal to resolve problems, such as copyright infringement and royalty sharing with outside producers and distributors.<br />
h. Consult with product development on product specifications such as packaging.<br />
i. Maintain awareness and understanding of competitive landscape.<br />
j. Occasional writing of marketing materials.<br />
3) Conduct pre-negotiation investigations of contracts with vendors and distributors to assist with product distribution, establishing distribution networks and developing relationships.<br />
4) Assist with evaluation of the financial aspects of product development, such as budgets, expenditures, research and development allocations, ROI and PL projections.<br />
a. Provide input to cost and markup factors as well as provide recommendations on promotional pricing strategies.<br />
b. Use sales forecasting and strategic planning to ensure the sale and profitability of products, lines, or services, analyzing business developments and monitoring market trends.<br />
5) Provide support for Events, PR, Customer Service and Research as well as other divisional support.<br />
a. Researching and developing content for management team presentations.<br />
b. Assisting with internal communications.<br />
6) Given this is a start-up environment, there is an all-hands-on-deck work ethic so there will be various other duties beyond the traditional marketing manager role.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
Required Skills and Qualifications:<br />
 <br />
&bull; 7-10 years of marketing experience with specific focus on online-advertising and other non-traditional media, direct response, branding and collateral)<br />
&bull; Demonstrated understanding of marketing concepts<br />
&bull; Knowledge of technology industry and launching new technology is an asset<br />
&bull; Able to work with and without supervision and with limited budgets and resources<br />
&bull; Experience in US market also considered an asset<br />
&bull; Post secondary education in Marketing an asset<br />
&bull; Strong initiative, time management, and project management skills<br />
&bull; Excellent written and verbal communication skills<br />
&bull; Ability to multi-task under tight deadlines and in a team environment<br />
&bull; Ability to work accurately (attention to detail) in a fast-paced, rapidly changing environment<br />
&bull; A positive friendly manner and customer service approach (both internal and external) that will enable you to deal with challenging situations with empathy, transparency and sincerity  <br />
&bull; Strong knowledge of Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, Power Point)</p>
